### Dependency Injection

**Clean Architecture:** each feature has its own DI file at the feature root (e.g. `login_di.dart`). The main `locator.dart` only orchestrates those setup functions.

#### Rules
- Use precise names (`DashboardBloc`, `login_di.dart`)
- Register services and repositories with `registerLazySingleton`
- Register BLoCs with **`registerFactory`** only (new instance per screen; prevents state pollution)
- Register use cases with `registerLazySingleton` (or `registerFactory` when a fresh instance is required)
- Register every new UseCase, Bloc, and Repository in the feature DI file
- Register `LocaleCubit` (or similar app-wide cubits) with `registerLazySingleton`
- Use `unregister<T>()` for dynamic values (e.g. tokens) that must be replaced
- Prefer a single GetIt instance named `locator` everywhere (do not mix `locator` and `getIt`)

#### Main locator.dart
```dart
import 'package:get_it/get_it.dart';
import 'package:project/features/login/login_di.dart';
import 'package:project/features/dashboard/dashboard_di.dart';

final GetIt locator = GetIt.instance;

Future<void> setupLocator() async {
  await setupLoginLocator(locator);
  await setupDashboardLocator(locator);
}

/// Replaces a previously registered access token.
void registerAccessToken(String token) {
  if (locator.isRegistered<String>(instanceName: 'accessToken')) {
    locator.unregister<String>(instanceName: 'accessToken');
  }
  locator.registerSingleton<String>(token, instanceName: 'accessToken');
}
```

#### Feature DI example (login_di.dart)
```dart
import 'package:get_it/get_it.dart';

Future<void> setupLoginLocator(GetIt locator) async {
  // Data sources
  locator.registerLazySingleton<UserRemoteDataSource>(
    () => UserRemoteDataSourceImpl(client: locator()),
  );
  locator.registerLazySingleton<UserLocalDataSource>(
    () => UserLocalDataSourceImpl(sharedPreferences: locator()),
  );

  // Repository
  locator.registerLazySingleton<UserRepository>(
    () => UserRepositoryImpl(
      remoteDataSource: locator(),
      localDataSource: locator(),
      networkInfo: locator(),
    ),
  );

  // Use cases
  locator.registerLazySingleton(() => GetUser(locator()));

  // Bloc — always factory
  locator.registerFactory(() => UserBloc(getUser: locator()));
}
```
